<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08222</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROFESSIONALIZING THE PRACTICE OF AUDIOLOGY AND CREATING FOR THIS PURPOSE A PROFESSIONAL REGULATORY BOARD OF AUDIOLOGY, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR, UPGRADING AUDIOLOGIC EDUCATION, INTEGRATING AUDIOLOGISTS, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to address the need for a regular study on the prevalence, development and causes of hearing-related diseases, impairment, and disabilities and strengthen the practice of Audiology to resolve the grossly insufficient number of audiologists.

Provides for the scope of the practice; prohibition against the unauthorized practice; disclosure of authority to practice; the Professional Regulatory Board; board examinations; registration and licensure; technical panel on education; and professional ethical standards.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-11-21)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2018-09-18</td></tr></table>